cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.NE 

The paper deals with deep learning technologies applied to medical image registration, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel registration framework that involves unsupervised learning, which suggests that it could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves information theory and neural networks, which could place it under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
